top.value: Federal Trade Commission (FTC) assistance to foreign antitrust agencies aimed at ensuring that competition agencies in developing and transitional economies that review suspected anticompetitive conduct and mergers share in a convergent approach to enforcement, analysis, and fairness, with a secondary goal of promoting competition in the economy at-large and cross-border cooperation.

Federal Trade Commission (FTC) assistance to foreign consumer protection and privacy agencies aimed at building a foundation for strong cooperative relationships between the FTC and newer consumer protection agencies with an eye to building the capacity of those agencies to serve as effective civil law enforcement partners in the fight against cross-border fraud, with the secondary goal of promoting a common vision of sound consumer policy.
